Think of it this way:<br>
FOT is 500 mana 2K dam<br>
Maelstrom of thunder is 3X900= 2700 dam for 440 mana.<br>
<br>
Lets say you have 1 wave resisted, you are at 1800 dam for 440 mana which is about the same ratio as FOT. Add in crits (1800, and you crit A LOT with pop crit ability maxed) and you will see that you do way more dam than with FOT. Of course, its not as flashy as FOT when you crit ... Untill you get 2 waves crits in a row<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=promethiuz>Promethiuz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 104<br> <font color=#333333>(12/9/02 3:08:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1723.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Always...</span><hr size=1> I got a triple crit with Maelstrom of Electricity. Can't wai ttill I scribe Maelstrom of Thunder and try for that. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=228778">Promethiuz Magus 62 Arch Mage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
