<br>
As all else is equal, the only difference between FoT and MoT is the dd focus effect. Therefore:<br>
<br>
FoT = 2000 (x1.15 for dd focus) / 500 mana<br>
MoT = 2700 (x0.70 for inbuilt resist mod) / 480 mana<br>
<br>
FoT = 4.6 ratio (plus SCM, Spec, Focus, etc)<br>
MoT = 3.9 ratio (ditto)<br>
<br>
However, this value of the in-built resist mod (chance to totally resist no matter what) for rain spells is based off historical values, and changed sometime ago to work off some other (unknown to me) formula <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . In a recent fight in PoP, I managed to cast 51 waves of SunStorm with only 9 resists. This gives an inbuilt resist mod for rains 0.82. So applying this mod to MoT gives:<br>
<br>
MoT = 2700 (x0.82 for inbuilt resist mod) / 480 mana<br>
<br>
MoT = 4.61<br>
<br>
This puts MoT SLIGHTLY more efficient than FoT, however it is based off ONE set of values which seemd exceptionally favourable considering my past experiences with rains.<br>
<br>
Rains are still good for thier low aggro aspect, but you're loosing efficiency because of it. However, that's a whole different discussion <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=38898">Salash Penumbra</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower">Summoner</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.midnightfury.org">Armies</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bgilles>bgilles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#333333>(12/10/02 9:22:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1723.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Always...</span><hr size=1> /shrug whatever Salash <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
