<br>
You can prove anything by picking data that will support your case. In this case, raw numbers for damage and mana prove favourable. However to get a true value of efficiency, an unbiased approach must be taken, where all variables that affect spell performance are considered. Some of these are indifferent and can be ignored. Others are quite sizable and must be factored in regardless. The remainder (those with small or negligable effect) can either be ignored or accounted for depending on how precise you wish your results to be.<br>
<br>
In the case of FoT + MoT, one of the largest variables (focus dd on FoT) has been ignored. This makes a significant increase in performance.<br>
<br>
