  55 Mage<br>
  50 Mage (me)<br>
  51 Ranger<br>
  53 Druid<br>
  55ish Beastlord<br>
  55ish SK<br>
The other mage cast boon of immolation, and I was in charge of casting malisement on the mob.  Once the SK pulled, I would immediately cast malisement on the mob, wait until it was at 80 percent health and then start casting rain of swords.  The other mage would also cast rain of swords and the mob would drop at an incredible rate.  Most times I didn't even have time to cast a second spell.  Everytime, essentially, the rain would hit for 324 hp damage x 3 once malisement was cast.  On average, about 1 in 12 rain waves would be resisted-- which is a lot better rate than i have previously encountered.  <br>
<br>
The evening was capped off by the SK saying, &quot;Jeez, why are these mobs dropping so fast&quot; to which the ranger replied, &quot;Mages&quot;.  Good times.<br>
<br>
Casala, lvl 50 mage (not for long) of Saryn<br>
