supposedly is because there was a bug long long ago that when a rain spell finished a mob off, ie: killed the mob, on either the second or third wave, for some reason, the game didn't understand where the damage came from (in laymans terms) and thus made the corpse poof. Similar problems long long ago happened when a DoT killed a mob off, and the corpse poofed. Now supposedly this bug is fixed, but rains are still resisted almost 100% of the time when the mob goes below say 8% life. I've got a few through, even killed a mob with a rain, and the corpse did not poof, so I assume this problem was fixed, but they are still resisted. Every other time though, the 3 waves seem to act like any other spell, with partial resists, the occasional full resist on a wave. the beauty behind it is, if FoT is resisted, you just out 500 mana. If Sunstorm is resisted with 1 wave, you still got 2 more to give some backup dmg. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bgilles>bgilles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#333333>(12/12/02 3:07:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1723.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Rain spells...</span><hr size=1> Yeah, dont use rains if the mob is at 15% health or so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wayfarerman>WayfarerMan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 305<br> <font color=#333333>(12/12/02 3:22:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http: